[3] Ecuador
Date: 25 Mar 2006
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: CRE Satelital, Ecuador, 24 Mar 2006 [translated by Mod.JGM, edited]
<http://www.cre.com.ec/noticias/detallenoticiasnac.asp?id=81367>

5 new cases of hemorrhagic dengue fever in Guayaquil
----------------------------------------------------
5 new cases of hemorrhagic dengue fever were lately confirmed in Guayaquil,
Guayas province. Affected people are being treated in the Infectious
Diseases Hospital, according to the Gamavision TV station. During this
week, the aforementioned health center received 15 patients with symptoms
of this serious disease. So far in 2006, 57 cases of dengue hemorrhagic
fever have been reported, 4 of them were fatal.
